{"created":"2014-11-05T02:00:34+00:00","modified":"2015-05-14T17:01:12+00:00","valid":{"from":"2014-11-04T20:00:14+00:00","to":"3014-11-04T20:00:14+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","tags":["Final Note","consumer spending","beer","elections","midterm elections","APM","Elections","election spending"],"published":"2014-11-04T20:00:14+00:00","itags":["1724644b7832615bd14c9d2801f2de45","Marketplace for Tuesday November 4, 2014","PMP:Marketplace_PMP","Marketplace"],"contenttemplated":"[{\"content\":\"<p>Let&apos;s take a moment to put the midterm elections in <a href=\\\"http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2014/11/04/americans-spend-16-times-as-much-on-beer-as-on-2014-midterms/?mod=e2tw\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">context</a>:</p>\",\"type\":\"text/html\"},{\"type\":\"text/html\",\"content\":\"<div class=\\\"large blue awesome\\\">$3.67 billion</div>\"},{\"type\":\"text/html\",\"content\":\"<div> </div>\"},{\"content\":\"<div class=\\\"large blue awesome\\\">$59.9 billion</div>\",\"type\":\"text/html\"},{\"type\":\"text/html\",\"content\":\"<div> </div>\"},{\"content\":\"<a href=\\\"http://www.bea.gov/iTable/print.cfm?fid=33765B426E012B0F46C01C6C5FF9C1BCCD3BE69200E9ACBED61EB489B6520F732B9EB466E44E4271B429CE74D833A631644F27231C9CFA4DC4F03C5A988F3C5B\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Bureau of Economic Analysis</a>\",\"type\":\"text/html\"},{\"content\":\"<p>At least we know where our priorities stand. Now would someone pass me a beer?</p>\",\"type\":\"text/html\"}]","title":"We spend more on beer than elections","byline":"Kai Ryssdal","contentencoded":"<div class=\"barn-cleaned\"><p>Let's take a moment to put the midterm elections in <a href=\"http://blogs.wsj.com/washwire/2014/11/04/americans-spend-16-times-as-much-on-beer-as-on-2014-midterms/?mod=e2tw\" target=\"_blank\">context</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"large blue awesome\">$3.67 billion</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\nThat's how much we spent on the House and Senate midterm elections, according to the Center for Responsive Politics.\n<div class=\"large blue awesome\">$59.9 billion</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\nThat's how much we spent on beer last year according to the <a href=\"http://www.bea.gov/iTable/print.cfm?fid=33765B426E012B0F46C01C6C5FF9C1BCCD3BE69200E9ACBED61EB489B6520F732B9EB466E44E4271B429CE74D833A631644F27231C9CFA4DC4F03C5A988F3C5B\" target=\"_blank\">Bureau of Economic Analysis</a>.\n<p>At least we know where our priorities stand. Now would someone pass me a beer?</p></div>","teaser":"Yes. Pass me one.","description":"Yes. Pass me one.","guid":"1724644b-7832-4615-8d14-9d2801f2de45","audio":[{"type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"width":"610","crop":"primary","height":"340"},"href":"http://www.marketplace.org/sites/default/files/styles/primary-image-610x340/public/beer_4.jpg?itok=p_LuKp3Y"},{"type":"audio/mpeg","meta":{"api":{"type":"application/json","href":"http://api.publicradio.org/audio/v2?ref=pmp&id=apm-audio:/marketplace/segments/2014/11/04/mp_20141104_seg_25"},"duration":42,"duration_hms":"00:00:42"},"href":"http://play.publicradio.org/pmp/d/podcast/marketplace/segments/2014/11/04/mp_20141104_seg_25_64.mp3","format":"MP3"}]}